		  <question>
		  <para>A regulation squash ball weighs 
          <unit_number><number>24</number><unit>g</unit></unit_number>. In a squash match
          a ball bounces off the back wall in the direction of the front wall 
          at <unit_number><number>1</number><unit>m·s<sup>-1</sup></unit></unit_number>
          before a player hits it with a racquet. After being struck towards the front
          wall the ball is moving at 
          <unit_number><number>20</number><unit>m·s<sup>-1</sup></unit></unit_number>. What
          is the change in momentum? 
          </para>  
		</question>
            <answer>
              <workstep>
                <title>Identify the information given and what is asked</title>
                <para>The question explicitly gives a number of values which we identify and 
                convert into SI units:</para>
                <list list-type="bulleted">
                  <item>
                    <para>the ball's mass (m = <unit_number><number>24</number><unit>g</unit></unit_number>=<unit_number><number>0.024</number><unit>kg</unit></unit_number>),</para>
                  </item>
                  <item>
                    <para>the ball's initial velocity (<latex>\vec{v}_{i}=<unit_number><number>1</number><unit>m·s<sup>-1</sup></unit></unit_number></latex>) towards the front wall, and</para>
                  </item>
                  <item>
                    <para>the ball's final velocity (<latex>\vec{v}_{f}=<unit_number><number>20</number><unit>m·s<sup>-1</sup></unit></unit_number></latex>) towards the front wall</para>
                  </item>
                </list>
                

                <para>We are asked to calculate the change in momentum of the ball,</para>
                

                <latex display="block">\Delta \vec{p}=m\vec{v}_{f}-m\vec{v}_{i}</latex>

<pspicture>
<code>
(0,-1.5)(12,5)
\psline[linecolor=orange]{-&gt;}(2,4)(4,4)
\uput[u](3,4){$\vec{p}_i$}
\pscircle[fillcolor=yellow!80!black,fillstyle=solid,shadow=true](2,4){9pt}

% Wall

%\psframe[fillcolor=gray!50!white,fillstyle=solid,linecolor=gray!70!white](5,4.75)(5.15,3.25)
\psframe[fillcolor=gray!50!white,fillstyle=solid,linecolor=gray!70!white](5,2.75)(5.15,1.25)
\psline[linestyle=dotted,linecolor=gray!30!black](1,3)(11,3)
\psline[linestyle=dotted,linecolor=gray!30!black](1,1)(11,1)

\psline[]{-&gt;}(6,2)(10,2)
\uput[u](8,2){$\vec{p}_f$}
\pscircle[fillcolor=yellow!80!black,fillstyle=solid,shadow=true](6,2){9pt}

\rput(1,0){
\psline[linecolor=orange,linewidth=1.5pt]{-&gt;}(3,0)(5,0)
\psline[linecolor=blue]{-&gt;}(5,-0.5)(7,-0.5)
\psdot(3,0)
\psline[linecolor=blue,linestyle=dotted]{-}(5,-0.5)(5,0)
\psline[linecolor=blue,linestyle=dotted]{-}(7,-0.5)(7,0)
\psline[]{-&gt;}(3,0)(7,0)
\uput[u](5,0){$\vec{p}_f$}
\uput[u](4,0){$\vec{p}_i$}
\uput[d](6,-0.5){$\Delta\vec{p}=\vec{p}_f-\vec{p}_i$}
}

</code>
</pspicture>
                

                <para>We have everything we need to find <latex>\Delta \vec{p}</latex>. 
                </para>
              </workstep>
              <workstep>
                <title>Choose a frame of reference</title>
                <para>Let us choose towards the front wall as the positive direction.</para>
              </workstep>
              <workstep>
                <title>Do the calculation and quote the answer</title>
                <latex display="block">
\begin{align}
 \Delta \vec{p}&amp; = m\vec{v}_{f}-m\vec{v}_{i} \\ 
&amp; = \left(<number>0.024</number>\right)\left(20\right)-\left(<number>0.024</number>\right)\left(+1\right) \\ 
&amp; = \left(<number>0.48</number>\right)-\left(<number>0.024</number>\right) \\ 
&amp; = <number>0.456</number> \\ 
&amp; = <unit_number><number>0.46</number><unit>kg·m·s<sup>-1</sup></unit></unit_number>~\text{towards the front wall} 
\end{align}</latex>
</workstep>
</answer>
</worked_example>

