          <para>The total momentum of the system after the collision, <latex>\vec{p}_{Tf}</latex> is:</para>
          

          <latex>\vec{p}_{Tf}={m}_{1}\vec{v}_{f1}+{m}_{2}\vec{v}_{f2}</latex>
          





          <para>This system of two balls is isolated since there are no external forces acting on the balls. Therefore, by the principle of conservation of linear momentum, the total momentum before the collision is equal to the total momentum after the collision. This gives the equation for the conservation of momentum in a collision of two objects,</para>
