                  <para>Momentum is conserved in all collision so it makes sense to begin
                  with momentum. Therefore:</para>
                  
                  <latex display='block'>
			\begin{align}
			 \vec{p}_{Ti}&amp; = \vec{p}_{Tf}\\
			 {m}_{1}\vec{v}_{i1}+{m}_{2}\vec{v}_{i2}&amp; = {m}_{1}\vec{v}_{f1}+{m}_{2}\vec{v}_{f2}\\
			 \left(0,3\right)\left(0\right)+\left(0,3\right)\left(-2\right)&amp; = \left(0,3\right){v}_{f1}+0\\
